Informed Consent Document for Apitherapy Treatment
Apitherapy is the art of healing using honeybee products, including: honey, pollen, propolis, royal jelly, beeswax, and bee venom. The patient and the apitherapist must build a relationship of trust between them for the purpose of joint work and the success of the treatment.
I, {{patientName}} ID: {{identityNumber}} (hereinafter: "The Patient") undertake, agree, declare, and confirm that:
Apitherapy is not a treatment method recognized by the Israeli Ministry of Health as a medical treatment.
Apitherapy treats the body and mind.
The Israeli Ministry of Health is not familiar with information and studies conducted in Apitherapy.
I am aware that during and/or as a result of the treatment, problems may arise, including but not limited to: itching, swelling, inflammation, wounds, temporary discomfort, and allergic reaction.
It has been clarified to me that an allergic reaction may manifest in various responses, ranging from a skin rash to total anaphylactic shock, including: breathing difficulties, loss of consciousness, and even death (if not treated correctly and promptly). Should I have an allergic reaction of any kind, I authorize and instruct irrevocably {{caretakerName}} 
("The Apitherapist" or "The Caregiver") to provide me with antihistamine medications according to their sole discretion if necessaryâ€”including an Epiphen injection.
The Apitherapist has not given or presented to me guarantees of any kind regarding the results and/or effectiveness of the treatment in Apitherapy.
I have decided, of my own volition, following recommendations I received and after preliminary examinations I conducted on the subject, to treat myself using Apitherapy in order to achieve relief from pain, health enhancement, and/or improvement of my physical and mental state, without relying on representations that the Apitherapist presented to me, if any were presented.
I have presented to the Apitherapist, in full, my entire medical/health history, including problems, treatments, and surgeries I have undergone, medications I have taken and am currently taking. Additionally, I confirm that I do not need to take beta-blocker medications.
In addition to my examinations and the recommendations I received, and without prejudice to the stated in section 7, and after deciding to treat myself using Apitherapy, I confirm that the Apitherapist gave me full information about the treatment plan, and I received from them a clear and comprehensive explanation regarding the risks involved in Apitherapy treatment, which, as stated, can even lead to death. I have discussed the subject with the Apitherapist and I am satisfied with the information in my possession and that which I received from the Apitherapist, and I have all the information required for me to understand the risks and the benefit of the treatment, and I take upon myself exclusively full responsibility for the results of the treatment, and I waive finally and irrevocably any claim and/or demand and/or lawsuit against the Apitherapist regarding the success and/or effectiveness and/or results of the treatment.